### 1.5 Webhook Signature Verification (CRITICAL)

**P24 Webhook** (`apps/backend/src/api/webhooks/p24/route.ts`):
```typescript
export async function POST(req: MedusaRequest, res: MedusaResponse) {
  const { sessionId, orderId, amount, currency, sign } = req.body;

  // Weryfikuj PRZED jakąkolwiek logiką
  const expectedSign = md5(`${sessionId}|${orderId}|${amount}|${currency}|${process.env.P24_CRC}`);
  if (sign !== expectedSign) {
    console.error("[P24 Webhook] Invalid signature");
    return res.status(401).json({ error: "Invalid signature" });
  }

  // Idempotency check
  const existing = await db.webhookEvents.findUnique({ where: { event_id: sessionId } });
  if (existing) {
    return res.status(200).json({ message: "Already processed" });
  }

  // Teraz dopiero verify transaction w P24 API
  const verifyResponse = await fetch(`${p24ApiUrl}/transaction/verify`, {
    method: "POST",
    body: JSON.stringify({ sessionId, orderId, amount }),
    signal: AbortSignal.timeout(30_000),
  });
  // ...

  // Zapisz event ID do idempotency
  await db.webhookEvents.create({ data: { event_id: sessionId, provider: "p24", processed_at: new Date() } });
  return res.status(200).json({ message: "OK" });
}
```

**NEVER**: Nie ufaj query params w URL (`?status=success`). Zawsze pull status z API providera PO weryfikacji podpisu.

