### 2.4 Payment Reconciliation Cron (MUST)

**Problem**: P24 webhook zginie (sieć, restart) → order wisi `pending` na wieczność.

**Solution**: Cron co 15 min pulluje status z P24 dla pending payments.

**Implementation** (`apps/backend/src/jobs/reconcile-p24-payments.ts`):
```typescript
export async function reconcileP24Payments() {
  const pendingOrders = await db.order.findMany({
    where: {
      payment_status: "pending",
      payment_provider: "pp_przelewy24",
      created_at: { gte: new Date(Date.now() - 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) }, // Last 24h
    },
  });

  for (const order of pendingOrders) {
    const sessionId = order.metadata.p24_session_id;
    if (!sessionId) continue;

    try {
      const statusResponse = await fetch(`${p24ApiUrl}/transaction/status/${sessionId}`, {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${p24ApiKey}` },
        signal: AbortSignal.timeout(30_000),
      });
      const status = await statusResponse.json();

      if (status.status === "success") {
        await orderService.update(order.id, { payment_status: "captured" });
        console.log(`[Reconciliation] Order ${order.id} captured`);
      } else if (status.status === "failed") {
        await orderService.update(order.id, { payment_status: "failed" });
        console.log(`[Reconciliation] Order ${order.id} failed`);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`[Reconciliation] Failed for order ${order.id}:`, error);
    }
  }
}
```

**Cron Config** (`medusa-config.ts`):
```typescript
jobs: [
  {
    name: "reconcile-p24-payments",
    schedule: "*/15 * * * *", // Co 15 min
    handler: reconcileP24Payments,
  },
],
```

**NEVER**: Nie polegaj tylko na webhookach. Zawsze reconciliation cron jako fallback.

